At ScotiaTech we want you to be part of a team that is always in personal and professional growth, for this reason we are looking for our new Cyber Threat Intelligence Analyst.



What will you do?



Able to conduct research and analysis of emerging cyber security threats and assess the potential impact to the Bank.
Maintain general awareness of threat landscape in LATAM countries
Providing Spanish proficiency in LATAM focused reporting and presentations
Strive in creating quality technical papers documenting security threats, risks, and mitigation techniques.
Proficient in communicating situational awareness and technical intelligence to internal and external stakeholders and trusted partners.
Understand how the Bank‚Äôs risk appetite and risk culture should be incorporate into in day-to-day activities and decisions.




What do we offer you?



Growth opportunities
Diverse, dynamic, and multicultural environment
Benefits for your financial and emotional well-being
Competitive wages


What do you need?



Have at least 2 years of hands-on technical working experience in any of the following: network security, information security and/or network support.
Have developed capabilities in prioritizing and completing assigned tasks in a timely manner.
Working knowledge of various network principles, cyber security concepts, investigation procedures, and adversary techniques.
Strong analytical and problem resolution skills.
Familiar in evaluating and sharing Indicators of Compromise (IoCs), Tactics, Techniques, and Procedures (TTPs) via reports, formal briefs, and threat indicator sharing platforms.
Familiar in reviewing and recommending countermeasures across various security controls (IDS, IPS, SIEM, Web Content Filtering, etc.) to identify and detect known threats.
Excellent communication and presentation skills with the ability to present to senior-level executives as well as technical staff.
Broad knowledge of common cyber adversaries, attack vectors, intrusion tactics, and attacker tools.




